$ Airys Wasserteleskop

{ rem

In den 60er Jahren des 19. Jahrhunderts untersuchten Hoch, → Wissenschaft/Geozentrik/Personen/Wilhelm-Klinkerfues[Klinkerfues] und weitere den Einfluss der Lichtwellen. Dabei wiesen sie darauf hin, dass
der Aberrationswinkel eines Lichtstrahls beim Durchlaufen durch verschiedene Mediums (z. B. Wasser) verändert werden könnte.

}

1869 schrieb → Wissenschaft/Geozentrik/Personen/George-Biddel-Airy[Airy] im «Report to the Board of Vistors»
"
  The question of dependence of the measurable amount of sidereal aberration upon the thickness of glass or other transparent material in the
  telescope (a question which involves theoretically one of the most
  delicate points in the Undulatory Theory of Light) has letely been
  agitated on the Content with much earnestness. I have calculated the
  curvature of the lenses of crown and flint glass (the flint being exterior)
  for correcting the sperical and chromatic aberration in a telescope
  whose tube is filled with water, and have instructed Mr. Simms to proceed
  with the preparation of an instrumet carrying such a telescope.
  I have not finally decided whether to rely on zenith distance of
  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/Sterne/Etanim[γ Draconis] or on right
  ascensions of Polaris.
"

Im Report von 1870 schrieb er dann
"
  I alluded in the last Report to a telescope whose tube should be filled with water
  for examination of the coefficient of siderieal aberration where
  the pencil of light passes through a considerable extent of refractory medium.
  I have decided to sue it in determining the apparent zenith deistance
  of γ Draconis at the proper seasions of the year.
"

"
  But it is really a result of great physical importance, not only affecting the computation of the velocity of light, but also influencing the whole treatment of the Undulatory Theory of Light.
  -
  […]
  -
  I think myself justified in concluding that the hopothesis of Professor → Wissenschaft/Geozentrik/Personen/Wilhelm-Klinkerfues[Klinkerfues] is untenable.
" [ On a supposed alteration in the amount of Astronomical Abberation of Ligth ]


{ TODO

  In *Aberration and the electromagnetic field* beschreibt Gilbert Walker ein Experiment von Röntgen, von dem Walker behauptet, man könne daraus schliessen, dass die Erde den Äther mit sich führt und
  das deshalb eine Erklärung für die Aberration gefunden werden müsse - und dass sich Fresnels Gesetz mit den Fakten nicht verträgt.

}

